Description
-----------

Libra is a tool set to create and manage load balancers in an OpenStack
environment.

Tools
-----

  * libra_pool_mgm

    Python daemon that manages a pool of Nova instances.

  * libra_worker

    Python daemon that will receive messages from an API server via
    a Gearman job server to create/modify load balancers on the local
    machine.

  * libra_api

    Python daemon to act as the client API server.

  * libra_admin_api

    Python daemon providing an admininstrative API server primarily for
    libra_pool_mgm and libra_statsd

Running Tests
-------------

Tox is the best way to run the tests. Tox, if unavailable, can be installed
via the Python pip command:

   $ pip install tox

Once it is installed, run the tests:

   $ tox

Quick start for developers
--------------------------

Use the install_venv.py script to create a venv:

1. Install some system deps

    $ sudo apt-get install git python-dev python-pip libmysqlclient-dev

2. Install virtualenv

    $ sudo pip install virtualenv

3. Clone the repo

    $ git clone git://github.com/stackforge/libra

4. Change directory to the repo.

    $ cd libra

5. Create the VirtualEnvironment with all the needed dependencies

    $ python tools/install_venv.py

6. Activate the venv

    $ . .venv/bin/activate

7. Hack the code and have fun using for example SublimeText or your editor of
    choide!

    $ subl libra.sublime-project

You can test your changes either as in the "Running Tests" section
(recommended before sending changes to review) or via

    $ python setup.py testr

To test in your active venv.

More Documentation
------------------

You can build the complete documentation with:

   $ pip install Sphinx
   $ python setup.py build_sphinx
